name: Guthling
dex_entry: Hatched from a green egg. These birds seek balance in the world.

name: Guthbird
dex_entry: Now a juvenile, the bird flies great horizons in the name of Guthix.

name: Guthraptor
dex_entry: Known as a bird symbolizing harmony and balance. If it shows up, all is well.

name: Zamling
dex_entry: Hatched from a red egg. These birds align with Zamorak.

name: Zambird
dex_entry: Birds who fly over battlefields.They are known for enjoying chaos.

name: Zamohawk
dex_entry: During the Third Age these hawks were used by falconers under Zamorak.

name: Saraling
dex_entry: Hatched from a blue egg. They possess great wisdom from birth.

name: Sarabird
dex_entry: With age these birds gain evermore wisdom of law and order.

name: Saraowl
dex_entry: A herald of Saradomin. These owls align themselves to wise individuals who respects law and order above all else.

name: Chick
dex_entry: Newly hatched from an egg, these birds will one day be killed for feathers by adventurers.

name: Chicken Normal Form
dex_entry: Gielinor's finest creature and in great abundance. Their feathers make excellent arrows.

name: Dreadfowl
dex_entry: While it is unclear how it is connected to the evil chicken. They do share a dreadfull magic attack.

name: Chicken Varrock Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Chicken Diving Form
dex_entry: This chicken adapted to underwater life after its home was sunken to the bottom of the ocean.

name: Chicken Karamja Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Chicken Death Form
dex_entry: Serving as the steed of Frank, the fifth member of The Horsemen. This chicken has done nothing worth mentioning.

name: Chicken Bandosian Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Chicken War Form
dex_entry: The horse of Frank, the fifth member of the clan, 'The Horsemen'.

name: Rooster Normal Form
dex_entry: While seemingly unusable due to not laying eggs, they are great for getting up early.

name: Ernest
dex_entry: A coward went inside draynor manor as a dare. Now his shape reflects his spirit.

name: Rooster Karamja Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Oomlie
dex_entry: Strictly found inside the kharazi jungle, their meat is used in the renowned 'oomlie wrap'.

name: Rooster Bandosian Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Chicken Famine Form
dex_entry: The fusion of 4 different chickens sent to certain death. Its power is that of 4 whole chickens.

name: Rooster Varrock Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Chicken Pestilence Form
dex_entry: The Scientist Avalani sent several chicken into the sky to research the clan citadel. Not many returned.

name: Chicken Lizard Form
dex_entry: It is unclear wether it is a lizard or a chicken. Nor what came first, the egg or the lizard.

name: Chicken Undead Form
dex_entry: Chickens who died, but became reanimated. They mainly hail fromMorytania.

name: Chicken Mystery Form
dex_entry: A chicken without any clear purpose or meaning. The real mystery is why it exists.

name: EvilChicken
dex_entry: A chicken known to eat its fellow chickens. Bad to the bone. It attacks adventurers on sight.

name: Swordchick
dex_entry: With a beak mightier than any others, it faces any opponents on land or sea. One of the homunculus's greatest creations.

name: Newtroost
dex_entry: Pretentious and arrogant. It flexes its muscles and howls in the glory of itself and its creator.

name: Calf
dex_entry: Unsteady on their feet, they never stray too far from their herd.

name: Cow
dex_entry: While they produce milk, most adventurers prefer their hide to make clothes.

name: Super Cow
dex_entry: When a slayer comes near, the matriarch will challenge it to a battle so epic, only cowhide is left.

name: Cow Dairy Form
dex_entry: Dairy cows are specialized in producing the highest quality milk and can be milked by any passing adventurers.

name: Cow Undead Form
dex_entry: A cow who died in the ghastly lands of Morytania. Do not drink it's milk.

name: Cow Chocolate Form
dex_entry: According to several surveys, 80% of players prefer the Chocolate cow over the vanilla or strawberry ones.

name: Cow Strawberry Form
dex_entry: Strawberry cows come to be by feeding a dairy cow plenty of strawberries throughout its period of growth.

name: Cow Vanilla Form
dex_entry: It is said that if you shake a vanilla cow enough and use a bucket on it, it will create a milkshake.

name: Cow Harlequin Form
dex_entry: A cow posessing the rare qualities of its fellow cows. When slaughtered, the pink parts are usually left behind.

name: SkeletalOx Female Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Bull
dex_entry: Angry and impatient, these monsters do not like fashionable people in red.

name: Bull Elder Form
dex_entry: The apex of bulls. They are capable of knocking players over, and filling their stomachs for a slayer task.

name: SkeletalOx Male Form
dex_entry: An undead bovine who has lost its skin. They are great companions for teenage witches.

name: Trojan Cow
dex_entry: Fred the farmer collects balls of wool in order to create the ultimate cow. The trojan cow.

name: Cow Plague Form
dex_entry: The cows of Sophanem and Menaphos were cursed by the devourer, and are thus slowly awaiting death.

name: Minotaur Normal Form
dex_entry: Far smarter than regular cows or bulls, they reside in the Stronghold of Security for no apparent reason.

name: Minotaur Rune Form
dex_entry: Whenever they see humans with horny helmets, they will ruthlessly charge at them for a duel.

name: Unicow
dex_entry: An experiment crossing the purity of a unicorn, with the shape of a cow. It's purity it still in question.

name: Rat Normal Form
dex_entry: While very small, they are sometimes capable of killing kittens.

name: Giant Rat Normal Form
dex_entry: Too big for any cat to hunt. These rats lurk about in the wild in search of food.

name: Brine Rat
dex_entry: A rat who lurks in the brine of the sea. They hold on to brine sabres.

name: Giant Rat Blessed Form
dex_entry: Iban, son of zamorak blessed these beings. Making them stronger than regular rats.

name: Rat Hell Form
dex_entry: Demonic rats, they are MALICIOUSLY CRUEL to anyone and TOTALLY EVIL.

name: Giant Rat Hell Form
dex_entry: Bigger than before, they are now capable of UNRELENTING MALICIOUSNESS.

name: Shell Rat
dex_entry: A being so BRUTALLY ANTAGONISTIC it could not pass the custom. So it entered a coconut.

name: Rat Crypt Form
dex_entry: The crypts of morytania warped these small rats, hardening their skills and aggresion.

name: Giant Rat Crypt Form
dex_entry: Despite living in a crypt, this rat is beyond fat. All rats used to look more like this before.

name: Warped Rat
dex_entry: A rat warped by a necromancer. Opening its mind to psychic powers, but losing the sanity.

name: Zombie Rat
dex_entry: Arisen from death, they serve as guards to Melzar the Mad.

name: Giant Rat Dungeon Form
dex_entry: Rats adapting to the life in the dungeon. Their scars are from many battles with other rats.

name: Rat King Form
dex_entry: A rat so deadly it could kill kittens with a single strike. They are known to form rat courts.

name: Giant Rat King Form
dex_entry: A king rat who lived to become a giant. Its hedonism and cruelty grew correspondingly.

name: Albino Rat
dex_entry: A rat that has become white and with red eyes. They can not stop themselves from feasting on cheese.

name: Angry Rat
dex_entry: Formed by the anger of Tolna, shaped to a rat. It knows only anger.

name: Experiment 2 Form
dex_entry: The experiment of a witch. They fling ogleroots as their weapons.

name: Lamb
dex_entry: Woolless and unready for the world. The lamb only hopes to baa with its parents.

name: Sheep White Form
dex_entry: The favoured race of Guthix. Mostly sheared illegally by adventurers.

name: Sheep Plague Form
dex_entry: A sheep coloured to pretend there was a plague in Kandarin. This was instigated by the faction of mourners.

name: Sheep Black Form
dex_entry: Sheep born with black fur are worth less than white ones because their wool can not be coloured.

name: Ram Fluffy Form
dex_entry: Its horns signals its ready to fight other males for dominance.

name: Ram Shaggy Form
dex_entry: Not as easily sheared as sheep, these monsters enjoy to strike back at unprepared adventurers.

name: Ram Golden Form
dex_entry: Golden rams tend to be monopolised by the troll Lalli. But their wool can be used to create enchanted lyres.

name: Sheep Pirate Form
dex_entry: When a pirate accidentally said he wanted a 'pirate sheep' his crewmates gave him this. It was accepted into the crew.

name: Goat Billy Form
dex_entry: Known for eating mostly anything, these goats are great for controlling grasslands on the mountain.

name: Goat Desert Form
dex_entry: As they wander the desert near Nardah they sometimes find adventurers killing them for their horns.

name: Goat Mountain Form
dex_entry: Their hooves are so expertly crafted, they can climb even the steepes mountain. Despite this, they are often used for soup.

name: Gorak
dex_entry: Despite being found in another plane of existence, some made it to Gielinor to fight by Zamorak's side during the God Wars.

name: Sardine
dex_entry: A small and otherwise weak fish. But rich in nutrients and purines.

name: Herring
dex_entry: Not to be confused with red herrings from Sinclair Mansion. These fish live their entire lives in water.

name: Trout Normal Form
dex_entry: Capable of crossing great lengths of water to mate, these fish can swim an entire day without rest.

name: Swordfish
dex_entry: Sporting a sword-like nose, these fish are very territorial over their turf.

name: Trout Leaping Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Sturgeon
dex_entry: Its nose is long for territorial fights, as well as a handy tool for examining areas.

name: Trout Tropical Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Sailfish
dex_entry: Their sail allows them to travel at far greater speed than swordfish, making them exceptional hunters.

name: Thallasus
dex_entry: The beast of the sea, it has been known to drown even the biggest ships and seasoned fishermen on the smallest of whims.

name: Bass
dex_entry: Often dropped on the ground by adventurers. These fish often feel lonely and alone.

name: Salmon Normal Form
dex_entry: When it is time to mate, these fish will climb the baxtorian falls, avoiding the whirlpools, to find a mate.

name: Shark Normal Form
dex_entry: A fish sporting a great number of teeth that can be regrown. Adventurers like to eat these in large numbers cooked.

name: Fury Shark
dex_entry: It is unknown where these shark hail from. Some theorise they can only live inside lava.

name: Salmon Leaping Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Shark GreatWhite Form
dex_entry: The most dangerous of all sharks, these fish will lash out and bite anything they find or deem edible.

name: Shark Tiger Form
dex_entry: A shark only found in the middle of the sea. They sometimes get caught in the fishing trawler, but most expeditions end up a wreck.

name: Mackerel
dex_entry: During the reign of Captain Rabid Jack. A man was filled to the brim with mackerels as punishment.

name: Catfish
dex_entry: Despite it's name, it is not a cat. But rather a fish. The whiskers threw marine biologists off.

name: Shark Baron Form
dex_entry: It is so rare and golden that it is sometimes hung up on the walls of houses. A rare prize for fishermen.

name: Tarpon
dex_entry: A vital ingredient for fish oil, hailing from Waiko.

name: Seerfish
dex_entry: These fish are apparently distantly related to the mackerel, despite their uppity name.

name: DesertSole
dex_entry: Since it is only found in the desert. It hides along the ocean floor camouflaged.

name: Sillago
dex_entry: A rare fish from the arc. It scours the reef hiding from predators and looking for food.

name: Wobbegong
dex_entry: Despite its ferocious look, it is actully not a dangereous shark to humans and prefer to hunt small fish.

name: Karambwanj
dex_entry: A fish that is hard to catch, only catchable in Karamja. It is very poisonous.

name: Karambwan
dex_entry: An octopus whose method of being caught was a mystery to mostly anyone but the Tai Bwo Wannai. Nowadays everyone knows about it.

name: Whitefish
dex_entry: A rare fish that feeds on slimy eels. They can be crushed and used as bleach to decolour clothes.

name: Beltfish
dex_entry: A fish so long it could be used as a belt. Apparently this is how it got it's name.

name: Manta Ray
dex_entry: A deep sea fish usually only found through fishing trawlers. They taste delicious but are hard to come by.

name: Cod
dex_entry: A fish that often gets the blame for children becoming angry or aggressive to others. It is unknown why.

name: Rainbow
dex_entry: As it shines in every colour conceivable, it was almost fished to extinction at one point.

name: Shark Golden Form
dex_entry: A rare shark with a seemingly kind grin on its face. They are mostly seen in aquariums.

name: Pike
dex_entry: A fish known for its green colour. Only about half the pike fished by adventurers actually get cooked.

name: Monkfish Normal Form
dex_entry: Only found in the Piscatoris fishing colony, they are sought after by sea trolls who fight humans for the land.

name: AnglerFish
dex_entry: A fish that captivates its prey with a shining light. As they adore the light, it bites and swallows them whole.

name: Giant Carp
dex_entry: A carp that could single handedly win someone a fishing contest. But it's tricky to bait it.

name: Monkfish Fresh Form
dex_entry: Not to be confused with regular monkfish that can actually be cooked and eaten.

name: Monkfish Golden Form
dex_entry: A monkfish so rare, that it's hardly eaten. Most find their way to aquariums in houses.

name: GoblinFish
dex_entry: A fish that only lives in the caves of the Dorgeshuun. Its taste is said to be very unique.

name: Pet Fish
dex_entry: Unable to live beyond their fish bowl container. They become quite discontent with their limited life.

name: Gilbert
dex_entry: A fish who wanted to see more than the ocean... But ironically needed to see the world through the ocean.

name: Cavefish
dex_entry: Living its entire life in underground water, it is unknown if they can even see in light.

name: Rocktail
dex_entry: Hard as a rock. Even harder to bite. These fish are tasty treats to most adventurers.

name: Eel Slimy Form
dex_entry: An eel whose only defensive strategy is to be so slimy it can slip out of any situation.

name: Eel Cave Form
dex_entry: It prefers the water in caves. It had peace and solitude until the dorgeshuun realized their existence.

name: Eel Sacred Form
dex_entry: An eel that used to be worshipped in the past for its spiritual powers. Nowadays they are eaten like any other eel.

name: Eel Lava Form
dex_entry: This fish can only survive in lava and requires special methods to be caught. One is needed to enter the heroes guild.

name: Eel Infernal Form
dex_entry: An eel once feared as an eel from Infernus, dimension of demons. No one knows, or care for that since it tastes delicious.

name: Eel Mottled Form
dex_entry: Known for their mottled texture, these eels tends to be fished with the aid of falconry.

name: Eel Short Finned Form
dex_entry: Everything but appetizing, these eels are known for their many short fins.

name: Eel Salve Form
dex_entry: For unknown reasons these eels seem to have some lesser holy qualities to them.

name: Eel Dusk Form
dex_entry: Eels that enjoy lurking in the darkest of waters as to not be caught. When caught, they are anything but pretty.

name: Cave Moray
dex_entry: The biggest of all water-dwelling monsters of Daemonheim. The Cave Moray is a meal in itself for adventurers.

name: Vile Fish
dex_entry: A fish so vile, no one would ever attempt to eat one. Except maybe Thok.

name: Piglet
dex_entry: These small things serve no real purpose to farmer but to grow into mud wrestlers.

name: Pig
dex_entry: Rumours has it that pigs have a purpose beyond merely mud wrestling. But the farmer who spread the rumour refused to tell.

name: Pigzilla
dex_entry: The apex of all pigs. Its said no pig has ever grown bigger than the pigzilla.

name: Puppy Pup Form
dex_entry: A cute little pupper that would die for you. Whenever you leave home, it will stay by your door until you come back.

name: Puppy Mutt Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Terrier
dex_entry: In ancient times, these were used for hunting and detective work.

name: Sheepdog
dex_entry: Used to guard sheep. These dogs will bark at anyone out of line, or run them down a cliff.

name: Dalmatian
dex_entry: It is unknown how many spots a dalmation can truly have. The only thing we know is that some are brown and without any.

name: Greyhound
dex_entry: Known for their excellent speed, people use them for gambling in races.

name: Bulldog
dex_entry: Ready to fight at any moment. These dogs often get breathing problems.

name: Labrador
dex_entry: Genetically engineered to emotionally love everyone. Loves head pats too.

name: Corgi
dex_entry: Dogs that faithfully serve their queen, as long as they get lots of treats in the process.

name: Terror Dog
dex_entry: A dog warped by Tarn in order to find the salve stone, he never succeeded.

name: Stray Dog
dex_entry: A mangy mutt who wanders the street, looking for the occasional bone and adventurers to follow.

name: Muncher
dex_entry: A skeletal hellhound who served as the lord of death, Harold's faithful companion.

name: Hellpuppy
dex_entry: When a puppy accidentally fell to the infernal dimension, it comes back as a hellpuppy.

name: Hellhound
dex_entry: A shakroth type demon from infernus. They bite really hard if not fed.

name: Cerberus
dex_entry: Known for its 3 heads, it's unknown if the heads act as one or if they retain individual personalities.

name: Kitten
dex_entry: Small and curious about the world. A kitten will do anything to play with a ball of wool.

name: Cat Normal Form
dex_entry: Known for their rat hunting prowess, they have become a mainstay in Gielinor.

name: Cat Overgrown Form
dex_entry: Since it has now grown to full size, it has become too lazy to actively hunt rats. The cat simply can not find the energy.

name: Cat Lazy Form
dex_entry: When a wily cat does not exercise it becomes a lazy cat. Out of shape and out of motivation. Just like its owner.

name: Cat Wily Form
dex_entry: A cat trained to peak condition. Ready to strike at any rat it sees. They would fight a giant rat if allowed to.

name: Cat Purple Form
dex_entry: Cat made purple by the powers of a sweet-tooth witch. It is unknown if there is more to it beyond the colour.

name: Cat Hell Form
dex_entry: When a cat eats too many hell rats, they become a hellcat. Infused by the hell rats infernal energy.

name: Cat Post Form
dex_entry: Letters connect people, and cats connect cat lovers. The postcat is an epitome of them both.

name: Cat Sunken Form
dex_entry: Sent as an omen to warn the adventurer of a terrible, terrible future. A sunken future. It also removes special effect on command.

name: Bob
dex_entry: The reincarnation of Odysseus, the mighty panther who died in a battle versus the dragonkin. Really likes Fish.

name: Evil Bob
dex_entry: An evil tyrant of whom most who have seen rarely survive. He takes slaves in to put them trough cruel services like uncooking fish.

name: Pet Rock
dex_entry: Known as the best companion an adventurer could ever have. They will fetch any stick thrown.

name: Rock Polished Form
dex_entry: Created by betraying a friend and turning them into a polishing rock for the purpose of completing a quest.

name: Pillar
dex_entry: The Elder Gods created several Elder Artefacts. The Pillar was not one of them. Despite this, it killed Mother Mallum in one attack.

name: Rock Soup
dex_entry: A troll delicacy made by mixing a pet rock into a soup of cabbage. You can really taste the rock in it.

name: Slagilith
dex_entry: Most Slagilith are caused by unknowing adventurers animating the face of a rock. It becomes sentient and will try to kill them.

name: Rock Strange Form
dex_entry: These rocks are known to sneak into a player's inventory when they are least needed.

name: Rock Golden Form
dex_entry: These golden rocks are known to sneak into a player's inventory when they are sometimes needed.

name: Party Rock
dex_entry: They dance with the fury of a mighty statue. Having one at a party is sure to raise the roof.

name: Strykewyrm Freezy Form
dex_entry: The different forms of strykewyrms are well adapted and dangerous.

name: Strykewyrm Leafy Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Strykewyrm Sandy Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Strykewyrm Wildy Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Scorpling
dex_entry: While small, these arachnids pack a real punch if an adventurer gets stung.

name: Scorpion Normal Form
dex_entry: These scorpions are far bigger than most adventurers.

name: Scorpion Pit Form
dex_entry: Scorpions, often nesting in pits, looking for scorpionite to eat.

name: Scorpion Poison Form
dex_entry: The poison they produce is strong enough to kill a kharidian sheikah.

name: Scorpion King Form
dex_entry: Fighting its way to the top, it has become the apex of all scorpions in its group.

name: Scorpion Grave Form
dex_entry: This scorpion got its name for killing a grave digger who dug near a scorpion pit.

name: Scorpion Corrupted Form
dex_entry: Scorpion corrupted by the devourer, granting it power at the loss of its will.

name: Scorpion Reanimated Form
dex_entry: Unwillingly sent back to the mortal realm, this reanimated being just exists.

name: Scorpion Gauntlet Crystalline Form
dex_entry: Uncorrupted, these scorpions find their homes in the gauntlet.

name: Scorpion Gauntlet Corrupted Form
dex_entry: A corrupted crystalline scorpion, now no longer holding a light within it.

name: Scorpion Khazard Form
dex_entry: Generald Khazard's pet. It has been trained to fight his prisoners.

name: Scorpion Spirit Form
dex_entry: In the spirit realm they are known as vicious fighters preying on other spirit inhabitants.

name: Scorpia
dex_entry: A vicious and cruel beast ready to kill and eat anything willingly entering its domain.

name: Dreadnip
dex_entry: Small and fierce, they will run at any enemy they see trying to eat them

name: Peepling
dex_entry: Has a curious eye for everything. Many adventurers have gone mad from their stares.

name: Sneakrpeep
dex_entry: Some say they watch adventurers and their every action to learn. Some theorize they gaze into their soul.

name: Runtstable
dex_entry: Made by a Gorajo, it lurks the Polymore Dungeon for food.

name: Basilisk
dex_entry: With its petrifying gaze, anyone who challenges it without a mirror will be left a garden ornament.

name: Baby Mole
dex_entry: Small and harmless, it will one day grow big enough to destroy any gardeners dream.

name: Giant Mole
dex_entry: A pest to Gardener Wyson. This mole destroys the Falador garden from below.

name: Squirrel
dex_entry: Happily jumping around without a care in the world. They often forget where they bury their nuts.

name: Ravenling
dex_entry: Hatched from a black egg. They rarely leave their nest on purpose.

name: Raven Normal Form
dex_entry: Known to pick up anything shiny. If you find a birds nest with a ring in it, it most likely belonged to a raven.

name: Raven Nevermore Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Raven Spooky Form
dex_entry: It flies in the night while calling for its ghostly friends. Not many show up.

name: Raven Crystal Form
dex_entry: Said to be the harbringer of the end, their allegience is to Seren.

name: Crow
dex_entry: A flock of crows often lurks around cities looking for food.

name: Magpie
dex_entry: It picks up shiny objects from everywhere. But is most known by summoners for its horrible cockney accent.

name: Chinchompa Grey Form
dex_entry: Capable of running great lengths. All barbers in Mishtalin uses them as energy.

name: Chinchompa Red Form
dex_entry: While usually passive, if provoked, they will put their all into exploding as a last resort.

name: Chinchompa Gold Form
dex_entry: A chinchompa with a golden coloration. They sell for a wealthy prize but do not explode.

name: Vultling
dex_entry: Rarely leaving its nest before they can fly, they survive on scraps given by their parents.

name: Vulture
dex_entry: Preying mostly on carcasses, they are important to the ecosystem as they remove diseased bodies from the world.

name: Pengling
dex_entry: Young and immature, they mature fast as they learn of their oppressors.

name: Penguin
dex_entry: Secret agents of the K.G.P on an undercover mission. Easily bribed by fish and cowbells.

name: Penguin Clockwork Form
dex_entry: Penguin toy made of clockwork. If someone was small enough to fit, they could probably control it from the inside.

name: The Thing
dex_entry: A perfectly normal sheep. In no way is it collecting information about you to use against you.

name: Ping
dex_entry: A musician fighting against the K.G.P from the inside.

name: Pong
dex_entry: Rebellious in spirit its song invokes glee and glamour in penguins.

name: Penguin McGraw Form
dex_entry: A penguin wearing a hat to distinguish itself from other penguins similar to it.

name: Penguin Spy Form
dex_entry: The vanguard of the K.G.P who investigate everything related to humans and their world.

name: Penguin Agent Form
dex_entry: A agent from the K.G.P fighting endlessly to take over the world.

name: Penguin Disguise Cactus Form
dex_entry: Disguising themselves as cactus these spies roam the desert.

name: Penguin Disguise Rock Form
dex_entry: Next to a pet rock its hard to tell which one might pick up a stick.

name: Penguin Disguise Bush Form
dex_entry: In forests they stand perfectly still to not be spotted by anyone or anything.

name: Penguin Disguise Box Form
dex_entry: Hiding in boxes allows them to check urban areas for intelligence.

name: ExExParrot
dex_entry: Used to be a real parrot but they are no more, its gone, and it longs for the fjords.

name: Broav
dex_entry: With a great sense of smell, they are able to find anything from truffles to secret trapdoors.

name: Tooths
dex_entry: A creature created by the magic of the tooth fairy. They turn rotten if they eat chocolate.

name: Rune Guardian
dex_entry: Created by rune crafting wizards, this automation is easily influenced by runic energy.

name: Gnomey
dex_entry: Given to winners of the golden gnome awards. Most being for pity or lack of competition.

name: Sparkles
dex_entry: A tinsel snake celebrating christmas. They refuse to curl around a tree.

name: Bat
dex_entry: Using echolocation they find their prey. They usually don't come out during the day.

name: Giant Bat
dex_entry: One of the biggest bats there are. They have recently been hunted to make magic armour.

name: Warped Bat
dex_entry: A bat warped by unknown energy. They have become aggressive; but not necessarily that strong.

name: Albino Bat
dex_entry: Found in Mos Le'Harmless. These bats have lost all colour in their bodies.

name: Bat Box Form
dex_entry: Mostly used as court evidence, these bats are perfectly sheltered from sunlight.

name: Fruit Bat
dex_entry: Despite their vampyric cousins, these bats love fruit among all things. Especially papaya.

name: VampyreBat
dex_entry: Whenever it clings to it's enemies, it will not let go until it is full of blood.

name: Deathwing
dex_entry: A rare bat only found in the deep caves of the Kharasi jungles.

name: Shaikah
dex_entry: Feared as the scourge of Karamja. This beast is hard to fell.

name: Growler
dex_entry: The bodyguard of Commander Zylliana and the vanguard of the Saradomin army.

name: Phoenling Rebirth Form
dex_entry: A baby phoenix. A wonder unthought of for many millennia. It loves attention.

name: Phoenling Reborn Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Phoenix Rebirth Form
dex_entry: A bird born of fire, if it dies it would simply return from its ashes.

name: Phoenix Reborn Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Plant Strange Form
dex_entry: A plant that can grow anywhere. But if the fruit isnt picked it will attack.

name: Plant Stranger Form
dex_entry: A summoning familiar known to be even stranger than the strange plant.

name: EvilTurnip
dex_entry: A turnip so dastardly evil, not even demons dare to go near it. It gives the Evil chicken a run for its title.

name: Creature Cute Form
dex_entry: A cute and innocent creature that would never harm you, spy on you, or find your deepest, darkest secrets.

name: Creature Evil Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Baby Yak
dex_entry: A yak that can hardly growl 'baroo'. With long locks of hair, they eat any grass they come across.

name: Yak Normal Form
dex_entry: Making their home in the islands of Neitiznot, their fur and hide are used to make clothes.

name: Yak Pack Form
dex_entry: A companion to any and all adventurers, the pack yaks will not stop at any weight to bring gear to their summoner.

name: Yak Sacred Form
dex_entry: A Yak said to be holy and sacred. It's presence is an omen of good.

name: Yak ClueScroll Form
dex_entry: It carries a hefty amount of clue scrolls, but without any interest in reading them. Not that it has the ability to.

name: Yak Undead Form
dex_entry: When a yak dies, that is usually it. Unless they become zombie yaks.

name: Yak Snack Form
dex_entry: A yak tasked with the important duty of bearing the food supply for an entire winter, without eating it.

name: Minitrice
dex_entry: The smallest of all cockatrices. They may not even be able to petrify a human.

name: Cockatrice
dex_entry: Born of a rooster and snake, these monsters lay eggs to increase their numbers.

name: Guthatrice
dex_entry: A green egg corrupted to become a guthatrice. Their view on balance is rocky at best.

name: Zamatrice
dex_entry: A red egg corrupted to become a Zamatrice. They petrify any who defies chaos.

name: Saratrice
dex_entry: A blue egg corrupted to become a Saratrice. Their eyes gaze upon any who do not uphold order.

name: Corxatrice
dex_entry: A black egg corrupted to become a corxatrice. They get really sad when they find shiny things and they turn to stone.

name: Vulatrice
dex_entry: A vulture egg corrupted to become a Vulatrice. Hoarding the deserts for food, they often petrify their meal accidentally.

name: Pengatrice
dex_entry: A penguin egg corrupted to become a Pengatrice. It is unknown if it sides with the K.G.P.

name: Chocatrice
dex_entry: A chocolate monster full of anger over its state. Its gaze will turn monsters to chocolate.

name: Sproutling Summer Form
dex_entry: A sprout that changes its appearance depending on the season.

name: Sproutling Spring Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Sproutling Winter Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Sproutling Autumn Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Rue
dex_entry: A dragon made of runic energy. They are known to sometimes steal adventurers runes as snacks.

name: Monty
dex_entry: Unchosen by the people, they live only to claim revenge on their hated enemy. Refuses to rest until their blade tastes blood.

name: Zygomite
dex_entry: A mushroom hailing from Zanaris, the moon of Gielinor.

name: Abyssaling
dex_entry: A spawn from the abyssal realm. While young, they are very aggressive.

name: Abyssal Minion Form
dex_entry: A minion to the hive mind of the abyssal pathways. They wander the abyss in search of intruders.

name: Abyssal Demon Form
dex_entry: A demon from the abyssal realm. They are said to manipulate the fabric of space to teleport.

name: Abyssal Sire Form
dex_entry: An abyssal demon of phenomenal power. It acts as if the gateway to the abyss goes through its body.

name: Abyssal Leech Form
dex_entry: They make their home in the abyss where they attack anything they can see.

name: Abyssal Parasite Form
dex_entry: A parasite from the abyss. They cling to their host; sucking them dry of energy.

name: Abyssal Lurker Form
dex_entry: Gets their name from lurking the abyss. In Gielinor, they simply follow their summoners.

name: Abyssal Walker Form
dex_entry: Their name as walkers come from how their best trait is they have legs.

name: Abyssal Titan Form
dex_entry: A titan from the abyss summoned by a summoning obelisk. It's unclear if it enjoys to serve others.

name: Tz Kih
dex_entry: Smallest of the wild beings of the tzhaar volcano. They fly around in the fight caves.

name: Tz Kek
dex_entry: A fighter of the fight cave, they were originally builders of the elder god Fuh.

name: Tok Xil
dex_entry: They fire deadly spines out of their arms, projected by their own heat.

name: Tz Kih Spirit Form
dex_entry: CUPHOLDER

name: Ket Dill
dex_entry: A plague upon the tzhaar volcano. These monsters are hunted for their meat but are hard to catch.

name: Ket Zek
dex_entry: A strong monster from the fight caves capable of firing great balls of fire from their bodies.

name: Yt HurKot
dex_entry: It's unknown for what reason, but these monsters seem to heal stronger monsters of the Tzhaar.

name: Yt MejKot
dex_entry: Possessing great strength they are a threat to any challenger of the fight caves. They struggle with small spaces.

name: TzRek Jad
dex_entry: A small creature that loves exploring what lies beyond the tzhaar volcano.

name: TzTok Jad
dex_entry: A monster and king of the fight caves. Warriors who beat one are presented with a fire cape.

name: JalTok Jad
dex_entry: Superior variant of the TzTok-Jad. Opposed to being leaders in their own right, they become guardians of the imprisoned leader TzKal-Zuk.

name: Jal MejRah
dex_entry: Ancestor of the Tz-Kih. They fly around in the Inferno.

name: Jal Ak
dex_entry: Superior variant of the Tz-Kek. They are slow and powerful.

name: Jal Xil
dex_entry: Researchers conclude that it is distantly related to the Tok-Xil.

name: Jal Nib
dex_entry: Often referred to as 'Nibblers'. They are at the bottom of the food chain in the Inferno.

name: Jal ImKot
dex_entry: A monster found in the Inferno. They possess extremely powerful claws that let them claw at their opponents.

name: Jal Zek
dex_entry: Superior variant of the Ket-Zek. They hurl large, projectile fire balls at their enemies. They are also capable of reviving their allies.

name: TzKal Zuk
dex_entry: A dangerous entity that got imprisoned deep below the TzHaar City during the ancient times. Sacrifices are regularly send to keep it at bay.

name: Duckling
dex_entry: With huge self-doubts, they fear that they might be truly ugly. Its parents are unaware.

name: Swan
dex_entry: Possessing teeth infused with infernal energy and a scream that makes any grown man scared, these demons attack any who oppose them.

name: Duck Normal Form
dex_entry: Waddling along playfully through the falador park. Some say they can grow to enormous sizes.

name: Mega Duck
dex_entry: The biggest duck on Gielinor. At some point they will go on a holy pilgrimage to the far off land of Feldip.

name: Duck Cart Form
dex_entry: A duck that climbed on top of a cart and has since never moved. It is now the king of the minecart.

name: Platypode
dex_entry: Small and weak, they attack back with poison to any who harm them.

name: Platypus
dex_entry: A pest to any resort owners. These monsters make great pets for hunters.

name: Fledgling
dex_entry: Having just grown big enough to move, these monsters are ready to eat anything.

name: Dagannoth Normal Form
dex_entry: A monster that is the sworn enemy of the Fremmenik. They hail from waterbirth island.

name: Dagannoth Guardian Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Dagannoth King Range Form
dex_entry: The kings of the Dagannoth, each possessing great strength above any normal Dagannoth. They serve their queen.

name: Dagannoth King Magic Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Dagannoth King Melee Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Dagannoth King Range Mega Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Dagannoth King Magic Mega Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Dagannoth King Melee Mega Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Chaos Ele
dex_entry: An elemental of pure chaotic energy. Its powers and behaviour is unpredictable to any enemy or friend alike.

name: Chaos Ele Mega Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Bandling
dex_entry: Hatched from a brown egg, this little bird seeks only conflict.

name: Bandbird
dex_entry: If there are peaceful times, this bird will fly to great lengths to find a war to fight in.

name: Bandeagle
dex_entry: Used by bandosian warlords as weapons, their claws have felled many soldiers on the battlefield.

name: Zaroling
dex_entry: Hatched from a purple egg, its motivations and goal is a mystery.

name: Zarobird
dex_entry: It closes its eyes and remains in solitude. Some say their presence is empty.

name: Zaraven
dex_entry: Possessing dark powers unheard of, these ravens appear at the darkest of times to watch over the world.

name: Sereling
dex_entry: Hatched from a cyan egg, these birds shine in pure light.

name: Serebird
dex_entry: Peacefully jittering along, they love to sing in harmonic tunes.

name: Serepea
dex_entry: While not a great flier, they refract light in a great many directions due to their crystals.

name: Frogspawn
dex_entry: Unable to move, the frogspawn patiently wait for their bodies to grow.

name: Frog Normal Form
dex_entry: Denizen of any pond or lake, the frog will ribbit in the face of any foe.

name: Giant Frog Normal Form
dex_entry: A frog grown to large size. They are hunted by the Dorgeshuun for food.

name: Giant Frog Royal Form
dex_entry: A royal member cursed to become a frog. Only a kiss from an adventurer could ever save them.

name: Frog Bloated Form
dex_entry: A frog infused with swamp gas. They are not very mobile and are easy prey for Chompies.

name: Frog Balloon Form
dex_entry: A very gassy toad that has no ability to move. Only being held down by the rock its tied to. They hate their lives.

name: Toad Barker Form
dex_entry: A summoned monster from the spirit realm. They get their name from the sound they make when attacking.

name: Frogeel
dex_entry: An abomination made by the Homunculi. Part frog part eel, it does not comprehend its existence.

name: Spiderling
dex_entry: While small, these spiders are used by inexperienced mages for training.

name: Spider Giant Form
dex_entry: Capable of growing quite big, these spiders are usually not a threat to seasoned adventurers.

name: Spider DeadlyRed Form
dex_entry: Sporting the name 'deadly red spider', these spiders protect their eggs from hoarders.

name: Spider Jungle Form
dex_entry: Since they live in the jungle, they have a green coloration. This makes them invisible to see on maps.

name: Spider Blessed Form
dex_entry: Spider that is blessed by the son of Zamorak, Iban. They are led by their brood Kalrag.

name: Spider Huge Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Spider Night Form
dex_entry: They lurk the ruins of Daemonheim. But it is most known for posessing a hood that makes you invisible.

name: Spider Ice Form
dex_entry: It's body is made of ice, making it one of very few cold-blooded insects.

name: Spider Spirit Form
dex_entry: CUPHOLDER

name: Eek
dex_entry: A really scary spider who loves webbing houses for the spider queen. Not doing so is an offense and will leave a spider in your bathtub.

name: MinstrlWeb
dex_entry: It is customary for the lord of Death, Harold, to always have cobwebs in his house. If not, this spider will punish him.

name: Sarachnis
dex_entry: A spider known to be the leader of temple spiders. Looming from above to hunt its prey.

name: Venenatis
dex_entry: It finds its nest in the wilderness where it awaits for unwitting prey to ambush.

name: Spidine
dex_entry: Staring eerily at anyone with its many eyes. It is unsure if its life was a folly or a mistake.

name: Crayfish
dex_entry: One of the weakest water creatures there is. Very envious of shrimps.

name: Shrimp
dex_entry: Often one of the first things fished by adventurers, shrimp never stay alone.

name: Lobster Normal Form
dex_entry: Praised by some as the best food in the free world. They are mostly found by the Karamja docks.

name: Lobster Golden Form
dex_entry: A lobster so rare they are mostly found in player-owned homes. They are easily recognized by their blue shell.

name: Lobster Giant Form
dex_entry: These highly aggressive lobsters are only found in Witchaven.

name: Lobster Heim Form
dex_entry: Found near the shores of Daemonheim, these lobsters are quite big, but otherwise harmless to all.

name: Lobster Obsidian Form
dex_entry: A rare and elusive lobster. Fabled as an unbelievably rare creature, people are willing to pay 100k for one. Limited time offer.

name: Crab Red Form
dex_entry: Their pincers are designed to hold on to their enemies. But at this stage, they are too small to effectively use them.

name: Giant Crab Red Form
dex_entry: Capable of dealing massive damage, these crabs use their mighty pincers to battle.

name: Crab Moss Form
dex_entry: Once a year, crabs come out of their shell to grow bigger, but they are vulnerable while doing so.

name: Giant Crab Moss Form
dex_entry: These crabs are mostly herded by Mogres; ogres living underwater. Their meat is a delicacy.

name: Crab RumPumped Form
dex_entry: This small crab has been pumped with alcohol since its birth.

name: Giant Crab RumPumped Form
dex_entry: A crab pumped full of rum under the orders of Rabbid Jack. They are served as a delicacy in Menaphos.

name: Crab Dark Form
dex_entry: A small adolscent crab posessing dark power it will never unleash.

name: Giant Crab Dark Form
dex_entry: Crabs that are so elusive and rare that even expert fishermen have trouble fishing them. Or live long enough to return to the bank with them.

name: Crab Grey Form
dex_entry: While initially gray or blue coloured, they turn red when they get boiled alive.

name: Giant Crab Grey Form
dex_entry: They fight with their pinchers for rights to mate, but most end up eaten by sharks.

name: Knife Crab
dex_entry: By giving a crab a knife, it is said their attack power triples. They are a threat to behold as they dance.

name: Heim Crab
dex_entry: A delicious, cute, and sweet crab found in the deep ruins of Daemonheim.

name: WebSnipper
dex_entry: When adventurers Marmaros and Thok explored Daemonheim, these crabs would snip their fishing nets.

name: Blue Crab
dex_entry: Easily recognized by their blue shell, these crabs linger in the deep caverns of Daemonheim.

name: Crablet First Form
dex_entry: A small crab more known for what they carry on their back. Which can vary in a lot of ways.

name: Crablet Second Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Crablet Third Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Crablet Forth Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Crablet Fifth Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Crawler Cave Form
dex_entry: Crawlers who search for food all day. They once became famous due to a combat expert.

name: Crawler Chasm Form
dex_entry: A far larger cave crawler who might venture deeper into caves than their younger counterparts.

name: Crawler Monstrous Form
dex_entry: The apex of the cave crawlers. Their bodies are so solid, moss and plants have begun growing on them.

name: Winston
dex_entry: Small tortoises bred by the grand tree for use as mounts. They love cabbage.

name: Tortoise Normal Form
dex_entry: These large creatures are usually ridden by 3 gnome warriors, each using a different combat style.

name: Tortoise Warped Form
dex_entry: Tortoise warped by Aposandra but the experiment failed. They now lurk the poison waste sewers.

name: Tortoise War Form
dex_entry: A summonable tortoise that loves to carry items. Its offense is pitiable however.

name: Valluta
dex_entry: A guardian of Guthix sent to fend off the void invasion. It can finish off a pest queen easily.

name: Sea Turtle
dex_entry: These sea turtles sometimes get caught by fishing trawlers. Therefore, they are hard to catch in bulk.

name: Sea Turtle Treasure Form
dex_entry: Carrying a great fortune on its back, fishermen perceives it as a sign of luck.

name: Herbert
dex_entry: A small and plantlike being often confused by a toad by passing adventurers.

name: Xinachto
dex_entry: A guardian spirit who holds the key to the anima mundi of its world. It feels shackled to the body it has.

name: Cave Slime
dex_entry: A slime that seemingly absorbs nutrients as it goes. It's unclear if they possess a will.

name: Jelly Normal Form
dex_entry: A gelatinous blob of slime, what is inside it is seemingly skeletons and organs. It is unknown where they came from.

name: Jelly Warped Form
dex_entry: A jelly so warped it could never be served to anyone. It's insides are beyond comprehension.

name: Jelly Spirit Form
dex_entry: Even in the spirit realm there exists jellies. Eating humans will cause them indigestion.

name: AbbySpectr
dex_entry: Their bodies are covered in slime, no one but other ghosts would dare to hug it.

name: Salamander Green Form
dex_entry: A green swamp lizard usually found in Morytania. They love Guam leaves.

name: Salamander Orange Form
dex_entry: Apparently related to desert lizards. They can fire a fiery breath at their enemies.

name: Salamander Red Form
dex_entry: Usually found around lava, these Salamanders have a fondness for herbs.

name: Salamander Black Form
dex_entry: Found only in the wilderness, these salamanders are rarely hunted due to the dangers of the Wilderness.

name: Salamander Augmented Form
dex_entry: As a strike against the gods, a black lizard became augmented by the inventions of mankind. Now stronger than ever, it strikes back.

name: Gecko
dex_entry: As they have no eyelids they lick their eyes to make sure they don't dry up.

name: Chameleon
dex_entry: Capable of looking in any direction, shooting its tongue like an arrow, and colour-changing skin. This lizard has everything.

name: Bloodveld
dex_entry: One of the lower forms of Chtonian demons. They hunger for blood their entire lives.

name: Bloodveld Insatiable Physical Form
dex_entry: Often used as pets for Vampyres, these monsters will salivate upon even small whiffs of blood.

name: Bloodveld Insatiable Special Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Bloodveld Mutated Physical Form
dex_entry: A bloodveld experimented upon to truly understand hemomancy. The experiments failed.

name: Bloodveld Mutated Special Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Reaver
dex_entry: A faction of Virii pledged to defend and fight for Nex, champion of Zaros.

name: Armaling
dex_entry: Hatched from a pink egg. These birds seek to uphold law.

name: Armabird
dex_entry: Flying swiftly through the sky, these birds will fly to kingdoms that uphold the law.

name: Armafalcon
dex_entry: Hailing from the homeworld of the aviansies, they possess wings able to carry them anywhere.

name: Ungodling
dex_entry: Hatched from a regular egg, this bird needs a god to align with.

name: Ungodbird
dex_entry: Knowing that following a god is a folly, they want to prove to everyone that gods are of no use to them.

name: Ungodgeon
dex_entry: Fighting with no aid from the gods, the godless assume they are the true believers of Guthix.

name: Tumekling
dex_entry: Born of an orange egg, this bird holds a small orb in honor of Tumeken.

name: Tumekbird
dex_entry: Balancing atop its orb, it will stand still even in the biggest of desert storms.

name: Tumekibis
dex_entry: Balancing the orb along its tail feathers, it is said to only drop it if it has no strength left to fight.

name: Kerrit
dex_entry: As they refuse to help you see in the dark, their only use is as a makeshift weapon.

name: Snuffle
dex_entry: Running great lengths at surprisingly fast paces, only seasoned hunters seem able to catch them.

name: Popoca
dex_entry: Expelling fire from their husks, they seem to smell like bonfires. It's hard to let them out in the wild as they start forest fires.

name: Choloa
dex_entry: A very skittish creature that when agitated, will simply roll away. Sometimes it rolls down hills and gets mad it has to walk up the hill again.

name: Durzag
dex_entry: A airut commander under the god of Tuska. They seek nothing but destruction.

name: Yakamaru
dex_entry: A spirit guardian who fell victim to airut shamans. It now summons jellyfish to fight for it.

name: Chompy
dex_entry: A fat bird that has trouble flying. Ogres hunt them for food.

name: Jubbly
dex_entry: A bird so fat that it could feed an Ogre for an entire week. The trick to catching them is a secret.

name: Jubster
dex_entry: Created by the homunculus, their reserves of meat and fat are so large, that it could feed a family of 3 on lobster for a week.

name: Terrorbird Normal Form
dex_entry: Trained as mounts by the gnomes, these birds have no quarrel with fighting any who challenge them.

name: Terrorbird Warped Form
dex_entry: Failed attempts to make the terrorbird smarter warped it to become like this. It is a failure.

name: Terrorbird Spirit Form
dex_entry: A terrorbird from the spirit realm. They can carry a great load of baggage on their backs.

name: Wolf Juvenile Form
dex_entry: A young wolf who prefers to stay inside caves. Their favourite treat is cave mice.

name: Wolf Normal Form
dex_entry: They form packs and hunt together in a flock. This way, survival becomes easier for the pack as they collaborate.

name: Wolf Fenris Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Wolf White Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Rover
dex_entry: CUPHOLDER

name: Wolf Dire Form
dex_entry: A big and dangerous wolf from Arendar gates. They sometimes come down to Isafdar to hunt the unknowing.

name: Wolf Jungle Form
dex_entry: CUPHOLDER

name: Wolf Skoll Form
dex_entry: A big wolf said in the Fremennik Tales to be a wolf capable of even swallowing the sun.

name: Wolf Desert Form
dex_entry: CUPHOLDER

name: Wolf Hati Hati
dex_entry: A big wolf said in the Fremennik Tales to be the harbinger of Ragnarok, the events that end the world.

name: Wolf Spirit Form
dex_entry: A wolf from the spirit world. Its howl can scare and repel any enemy, making it a good companion for new adventurers.

name: Fox
dex_entry: A crafty and shrewd vulpine. Known for sneaking into chicken pens to steal food.

name: Inari
dex_entry: A fox that has lived so long it grew additional tails. Each tail gave it more power.

name: Helwyr
dex_entry: Sorcerer of the Cywir clan, it fights in the name of Seren with the power of the spirit realm.

name: Bird Nest
dex_entry: A delight for people who chop down trees. These nests often have small eggs in them.

name: Birds Nest God Form
dex_entry: The next holds a egg which will one day hatch into a bird.

name: Pigeon
dex_entry: Mostly harmless birds that enjoy looking down on people from coathangers in a scornful way.

name: Pheasant
dex_entry: Often seen with the Freaky Forester. These birds serve no purpose except being food.

name: Rocling
dex_entry: It's wings are not ready to fly, yet it hunts for goatweed all day.

name: Roc
dex_entry: Known by a local farmer as 'big bird'. It has large wings capable of knocking farmers over.

name: Foal
dex_entry: A young unicorn pure of will and naive to the dangers of the world.

name: Unicorn White Form
dex_entry: With a pure mind, the unicorn is said to grant blessings. They enjoy the company of virgins and pure souls.

name: Unicorn Stallion Form
dex_entry: A stallion from the spirit realm. With great healing powers, they help their allies in battles.

name: Unicorn Black Form
dex_entry: A unicorn corrupted by the dark will of man. It laughs at adventurers misfortunes.

name: Unicorn Angry Form
dex_entry: In Tolna's rift, these unicorns are the incarnation of anger, stabbing anything they see.

name: Unicorn Reanimated Form
dex_entry: Losing its holy and serene aura, these unicorns exist for no reason but to die again.

name: Starlight
dex_entry: The bodyguard of Commander Zilyana. Often annoyed, her employer is nicknamed 'Saradomin'.

name: Pawya
dex_entry: Native to Isafdar, these small critters love the taste of papaya, which are in short supply in the elven lands.

name: Grenwall
dex_entry: Hunters to the core. They prey on Pawya. If threatened, they will curl up into a defensive mode. Their spikes are used for potions.

name: Bear Cub
dex_entry: A young bear with much to learn. Easily tricked by honey. Tends to repay favours with an oblivious slap.

name: Bear Normal Form
dex_entry: A large monster of the ursa family. They will eat large amounts of food before hibernating in the winter.

name: Bear Reanimated Form
dex_entry: A bear reanimated through the power of the death altar. Killing them helps train prayer.

name: Bear Gauntlet Crystalline Form
dex_entry: An uncorrupted bear from the gauntlet. Shining in pure crystalline light.

name: Callisto
dex_entry: It can charge thundering blows that might stun anyone nearby. So it is best to avoid it.

name: Polar Bear Normal Form
dex_entry: A bear native to Archeron. They held penguins as slaves and are the sworn enemies of the seals.

name: Polar Bear PBJ Agent Form
dex_entry: Highly trained in the art of disguises, these agents are the vanguard against the K.G.P.

name: Polar Bear Arctic Form
dex_entry: A very curious bear from the spirit realm. They will seemingly entertain any audience in an informative way.

name: Polar Bear Nanuq Form
dex_entry: When danger approaches the kingdom of Misthalin, Nanuq will stand vigilant near a kiln to warn them.

name: Bear Grizzly Form
dex_entry: A bear, larger and stronger than a black bear. They spend most of their time in solitude.

name: Kendall
dex_entry: A god of the mountain. A cannibal posed as the Kendall once and ate whoever came close to his domain.

name: Bear Gauntlet Corrupted Form
dex_entry: A corrupted bear from the gauntlet. Its once crystalline body has become dirty with corruption.

name: Bear Angry Form
dex_entry: Anger does not even begin to explain what this bear is capable of. A pure representation of Tolna's anger.

name: Graahk Normal Form
dex_entry: A big horned monster from the Karamja jungles. Their horns are so solid, they will leave a dent on even steel.

name: Graahk Spirit Form
dex_entry: A graahk from the spirit realm. They are not as easily teased as their Gielinorian counterpart.

name: Dust Devil
dex_entry: A devil that makes a sound so dastardly any dog will bark at it in fear. It cleans up its domain however.

name: SmokeDevil
dex_entry: Expelling great amounts of smoke, it is hard to know if it does so to defend itself, or annoy its opponents.

name: SmokeDevil Nuclear Form
dex_entry: A monster said to be so unstable it could blow up at any moment. Yet it keeps on living as if nothing is a threat.

name: ChokeDevil
dex_entry: A monster who will make even a grown man choke on his own breath. Any who challenge it should wear a facemask.

name: SmokeDevil Thermonuclear Form
dex_entry: Said to be a danger to itself and any around it. It will refuse to do anything but harm those it loves.

name: Hatchling
dex_entry: A newly hatched dragon. When they eat, they sometimes burn their food and become grumpy.

name: Dragonling Green Form
dex_entry: A small dragon. Dragons were originally made by the dragonkin to relieve them of their curse.

name: Dragon Green Form
dex_entry: Sporting incredibly thick hide, dragons are killed for their bones and hide which sells for a good price.

name: Dragon Brutal Green Form
dex_entry: Scarred from battle, these dragon's are battle hardened and stronger than the regular kind.

name: Dragonling Blue Form
dex_entry: Small and cute, they have yet to breathe fire. They are still killed anyway.

name: Dragon Blue Form
dex_entry: A weaker dragon that can still pack a punch. Adventurers choose to kill them for trade.

name: Dragon Brutal Blue Form
dex_entry: A dragon that should never be underestimated. Aside from being coloured blue, they are distinguished by spiky horns.

name: Dragonling Red Form
dex_entry: A young creature secluded to the Brimhaven Dungeon. They make friends with dogs.

name: Dragon Red Form
dex_entry: A strong creature hidden away in inconvenient locations. They are not valued as high as their cousins.

name: Dragon Brutal Red Form
dex_entry: A dragon that should never be underestimated. Aside from being coloured red, they are distinguished by a pointy horn.

name: Dragonling Black Form
dex_entry: The elite of all baby dragon forms. They tend to stick close to their parents.

name: Dragon Black Form
dex_entry: All hail the feared black dragon. They were once believed to be the strongest monsters of all.

name: Dragon Brutal Black Form
dex_entry: A dragon that should never be underestimated. Aside from being coloured black, they are distinguished by curvy horns.

name: Dragon ThreeHeaded Form
dex_entry: A monster that should no longer exist. Finding one is a statistical anomaly.

name: Elvarg
dex_entry: Slayer of Crandor Island. Elvarg is a threat to be reckoned with for any unprepared adventurer.

name: Dragon King Black Form
dex_entry: A 3-headed black dragon made by Kerapac. Its real name is Shakorexis.

name: Dragon Queen Black Form
dex_entry: The first dragon ever created, laid to slumber as it serves to use anymore. Grotworms have since infested it.

name: Hand Creeping Form
dex_entry: A really small hand. So small, it would come in handy at any kind of on-hand situation. They hate puns.

name: Hand Crawling Form
dex_entry: A hand from Viggora's Folly, a tower that fell into the ground due to unstable foundations. They love rings and gloves.

name: Hand Skeletal Form
dex_entry: A crawling hand without any skin left. Some theorize there could be skeletal feet out there.

name: Hand Crushing Form
dex_entry: A hand so big it will crush anything it can. Despite lacking a body, it really packs a punch.

name: Hand Zombie Form
dex_entry: Perhaps you should avoid shaking the hand. It has been rotting for some time.

name: Turoth
dex_entry: A creature so persistent, only a broad type of weapons could ever wish to harm it.

name: Turoth Mightiest Form
dex_entry: A turoth grown to prime strength. Stronger than others of its kind, it will fight till its last breath to feed itself.

name: Big Turoth
dex_entry: Its size is far larger than other turoth's making it more dangereous. But not that much dangereous.

name: Sockroth
dex_entry: A turoth who, due to a number of inconvenient events and a fallout with Meg the Adventurer, now possesses a sock.

name: Lilrask
dex_entry: A kurask not fully grown yet. To prove its worth, it must travel to Karamja and return home with a pineapple.

name: Kurask
dex_entry: Having returned from Karamja with its prized possession, it is now marked an adult and can be a respected member of its herd.

name: Kurask King Form
dex_entry: The king of its herd. They lead their herd with wisdom and experience.

name: Kurask Overlord Form
dex_entry: It leads with a stern hand, demanding fruit as tribute for its protection.

name: Kebbit
dex_entry: A small monster mostly seen as prey by everyone else than other kebbits.

name: Kebbit Polar Form
dex_entry: A monster that defends itself with camouflage in snowy areas. It does not like the cold however.

name: Kebbit Sabre Form
dex_entry: One of the more dangerous kebbits, they have massive fangs that bite predators. They are not that smart however.

name: Kebbit Spotted Form
dex_entry: Their spots confuse predators by causing optical illusions while running.

name: Kebbit Dark Form
dex_entry: They can run at great speed without making a sound. This is due to their sleek fur.

name: Kebbit Dashing Form
dex_entry: These monsters are swift runners. Fast regular traps are no match for them. Falcons, however, easily catch them.

name: Kebbit Wild Form
dex_entry: These kebbits have grown small spikes in an attempt to defend themselves. But they got hunted even more by humans for trade.

name: Kebbit Prickly Form
dex_entry: A kebbit that is usually hunted by intermediate hunters. They hate falcons with a passion.

name: Kebbit Razor Form
dex_entry: These kebbits will lower their bodies to the ground and then throw their backs into their enemies for self defence.

name: Kebbit Big Form
dex_entry: A kebbit that has grown to an extreme size. Despite its size, it is still a weak kebbit.

name: Kebbit DesertDevil Form
dex_entry: They only live in the desert, despite there not being much food around.

name: Kebbit Feldip Weasel Form
dex_entry: One of the more common kebbits, hailing from the Piscatoris hunter area.

name: Kebbit Barbed Form
dex_entry: A kebbit with a barb tail so sharp, it can even be used to fish.

name: Kebbit Diseased Form
dex_entry: Being struck by disease, this kebbit awaits for it's life to end. Possibly dragging more of its kind with it.

name: Kebbit Chocolate Form
dex_entry: A kebbit made entirely of chocolate, usually by the powers of a chocatrice.

name: Monkey Normal Form
dex_entry: Denizens of Karamja, these creatures love bananas and playing tricks on humans.

name: Monkey Ninja Form
dex_entry: Monkey trained to prime speed and form. They defend the Ape Atoll from any outsiders.

name: Gorilla Normal Form
dex_entry: A stronger kind of primate that are used when the speed of a monkey is not enough, and raw strength is needed.

name: Monkey Zombie Form
dex_entry: Monkeys arisen by necromantic arts and locked away in the caves beneath the Ape Atoll.

name: Gorilla Ancient Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Monkey Harmless Form
dex_entry: The mohawk is uncoloured as opposed to its Karamjan cousin, making them more boring.

name: Monkey Ghost Form
dex_entry: They are the souls of monkeys who died in the process of making a colony.

name: Gorilla Ayuni Form
dex_entry: The Devourer stripped Apmeken of her sight, creating Ayuni

name: Gorilla Leeuni Form
dex_entry: Apmekens lips and voice given shape in a cruel avatar. Causing havock in the Desert.

name: Gorilla Eruni Form
dex_entry: Without her ears, Apmeken could no longer hear the pleas of her followers.

name: Monkey Karamja Baby Form
dex_entry: A small monkey often brought as pets by passing adventurers.

name: Monkey Karamja Adult Form
dex_entry: As they grow older, most of these monkeys are left in Player owned menageries to be forgotten.

name: Larupia Normal Form
dex_entry: A swift hunter from the Feldip region. Their fur is adapted to camouflage in the jungles.

name: Larupia Spirit Form
dex_entry: A hunter from the spirit realm. These monsters have really sharp senses, making them great partners for hunters.

name: Kyatt Normal Form
dex_entry: The apex predator of the snowy north. Their fangs are really sharp, but if they break, they cannot be regrown.

name: Kyatt Spirit Form
dex_entry: A kyatt from the spirit realm. Capable of teleporting it and its adventurer to where it pleases, when it pleases.

name: Crabling
dex_entry: So small it can hide anywhere, it needs to make a decision how to survive in the future.

name: Rock Crab Normal Form
dex_entry: A crab made of solid rock. They stay along beaches motionlessly. If a rock moves, it might be a rock crab.

name: Rock Crab Giant Normal Form
dex_entry: Far larger than it's smaller counterpart, it has become a lot harder to hide as a small rock.

name: Rock Crab Ammonite Form
dex_entry: They carry fossils on their back, unaware of their history.

name: Rock Crab Giant Ammonite Form
dex_entry: A crab so ancient, fossils can be seen on it. Archaeologists want to study them but are no match to their powers.

name: Rock Crab Sand Form
dex_entry: These crabs are mainly found in desert regions, using sand instead of rocks.

name: Rock Crab Giant Sand Form
dex_entry: In the warm desert its not uncommon to accidentally step on one.

name: Rock Crab Swamp Form
dex_entry: Mainly found in swamp's, they use whatever they can find as substitute shells.

name: Rock Crab Giant Swamp Form
dex_entry: As swamps get less and less stumps, these crabs are slowly going extinct.

name: Crab Granite Form
dex_entry: A bigger rockcrab from Waterbirth Island. They are far larger and deadlier but prefer to stay immobile.

name: Lobster Granite Form
dex_entry: A lobster from the spirit realm. Smaller and swifter, these lobsters are really good at fishing underwater.

name: Lobster Rock Form
dex_entry: A lobsters pretending to be a rock. Except it wasn't a rock, it was a rock lobster.

name: Rabbit
dex_entry: A creature that is light on its feet but are otherwise useless. Their meat is tasty and their feet bring luck to lumberjacks.

name: Wolperting
dex_entry: A rabbit from the spirit realm with antlers and magical powers. It also seemingly grants a great deal of camouflage to those in its herd.

name: Bunyip
dex_entry: A swamp creature from the spirit realm. They prefer to swallow their fish raw.

name: TalonBeast Talon Form
dex_entry: A feared monster of Morytania. It gets it name from the talons it possesses that has killed many adventurers.

name: TalonBeast Nail Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Ferret
dex_entry: A friendly critter not to be confused with the ferret of doom. These muspelids will gladly hunt rabbits.

name: Toy Mouse
dex_entry: An automation made of clockwork to mimic a mouse. Cats love to play with these.

name: Toy Doll
dex_entry: Toy doll made from clockwork. It pirouettes and dances whenever it can.

name: Toy Soldier
dex_entry: Made of clockwork, it seemingly follows its duty of marching to war. Even if there isn't any...

name: Cat Clockwork Form
dex_entry: An automation made of clockwork to mimic mans best friend. They refuse to meow.

name: Magicarpet
dex_entry: Magically infused carpets capable of flight. They are used as transportation in the Kharidian desert.

name: Anichair
dex_entry: A chair that has seemingly gained life. They love to play tricks on adventurers who enter their domain.

name: Exoraxe
dex_entry: An axe posessed by a ghost. Their movements are primitive, but deadly.

name: Spookaxe
dex_entry: A pickaxe possessed by a long passed away miner. Even in death it keeps on chopping at anything.

name: Dobbin
dex_entry: Toy of a being that is now extinct. A horse is apparently something like a hornless unicorn that tasted delicious.

name: Marionette
dex_entry: Marionette who dances to the puppetmaster. If there are no strings, it will fight back.

name: DragonKite
dex_entry: Sold due to high demand of Dragon kites. Adventurers got upset it was not a kiteshield and sales plummeted.

name: Animour
dex_entry: Armour reanimated by magic to become a test of strength. They are great for combat training.

name: Dead Tree
dex_entry: Just a normal tree without any leaves or life left. Something like this could never move.

name: Jadinko
dex_entry: Born of vines and plants, these monsters are one with nature and take many forms.

name: Killerwatt
dex_entry: A being from another plane. They are made entirely of electrical energy and will expel it at every opportunity.

name: Mackers
dex_entry: Unrelated to the K.G.P. The turkeys are trying to launch an attack on humans. Humans don't care since it is thanksgiving.

name: Turkey Female Form
dex_entry: Grown and ready to defend itself. It retaliates against adventurers to fight for its freedom. They are then eaten.

name: Turkey Male Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Turkey Protestor Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Toucan Tenacious Male Form
dex_entry: Tenacious to a T, they will relentlessly attack adventurers embarking into the jade vine.

name: Toucan Tenacious Female Form
dex_entry: Nothing Interesting Happens.

name: Toucan Tuai Leit Form
dex_entry: Despite the look of it, its beak is actually very brittle and prone to breaking.

name: Jellyfish Blubber Form
dex_entry: Its blue colorations are meant to disguise it under the sea. This makes it easier to fight prey.

name: Jellyfish
dex_entry: They are commonly referred to as 'melee fish' since they are very physically strong.

name: Pure
dex_entry: A chunk of runestone from a rock infused by the stone of Jas.

name: Rune
dex_entry: Infused with the energy of the runic altars, the rune essence gains the powers of the altars.

name: Essence
dex_entry: In large supplies, runes are capable of creating spells. But not knowing what to do with them might expel said energy.

name: Seagull Normal Form
dex_entry: A small bird often found amongst docks. They tend to clean harbours of food scraps otherwise left unattended.

name: Pelican
dex_entry: Pelicans lurk fishing platforms hoping to either steal a fish, or for a fishing adventurer to give them a treat.

name: Albatross
dex_entry: Flying around Cairn Island, these birds fish for food.

name: Seagull Hattenkrapper Form
dex_entry: Baron von Hattenkrapper. Sworn rival of Count Ludvig Koppenploppen. Known as the slayer of barrelchests on Bloodsplatter island.

name: Seagull Koppenploppen Form
dex_entry: Count Ludwig Koppenploppen. Sworn rival to Baron von Hattenkrapper. Known to have eaten many meals on The rock.

name: Seagull Steven Form
dex_entry: Flightless, the bird has nothing but it's own name that holds any value. It fights with all it has.

name: Ibis
dex_entry: Fishers with good summoning levels summon these birds to improve their catches.

name: DesertWyrm
dex_entry: A smaller, limbless kind of dragon that prefers to sail along the desert. The sandstorms cannot damage them.

name: Wyrm
dex_entry: A bigger, limbless dragon. While it has no fire breath, it is still a threat to unprepared adventurers.

name: Snake Normal Form
dex_entry: Found in the jungles of Karamja, these snakes are usually harmless to most travelers.

name: Cobra Normal Form
dex_entry: Their necks can enlargen to scare their enemies. They dance when they are charmed by a flute.

name: Cobra Spirit Form
dex_entry: A cobra from the spirit realm. They can corrupt eggs, making them into cockatrice egg's

name: Juna
dex_entry: Guardian of Guthix, this snake was set to guard the residual sadness of Guthix left in the rocks of lumbridge.

name: Snake Sea Form
dex_entry: Found deep beneath Misthalin and Etceteria, these snakes only live in underwater caves.

name: Big Snake Sea Form
dex_entry: Grown to a size far larger than any other snake, it preys on what enters its caves.

name: Thingumwut
dex_entry: They are said to be beings of immense power by the authority on the subject, Traiborn.

name: Experiment 3 Form
dex_entry: Made by Dr. Fenkenstrain, these experiments are either sheep in wolf clothing, or the opposite.

name: Cabbage
dex_entry: They pray each morning to their god Brassica Prime, the strongest of all gods.

name: Ughtanki
dex_entry: They roam the desert looking for oasises, escaping kebab salesmen who kill them.

name: Camel
dex_entry: The hump on its back stores water and moisture as fat. Allowing it to live in the desert.

name: Camel Warrior Form
dex_entry: These warriors uses their power over magic and illusion to confuse their enemies before killing them.

name: BalanceEle
dex_entry: Appointed as a guardian of Guthix. It guards the Stone of Jas while talking of your funeral.

name: Kalphite Larva Form
dex_entry: So small that even a cat could hunt them down for sport. Sometimes cats do just that.

name: Kalphite Worker Form
dex_entry: Workers of the hive. These kalphites are not meant for combat.

name: Kalphite Soldier Form
dex_entry: Kalphites born only to fight intruders of the hive. Their poison stings any adventurer.

name: Kalphite Spirit Form
dex_entry: Kalphites from the spirit realm has a stunning blue colour exoding glamour before they eat their prey alive.

name: Kalphite Guardian Form
dex_entry: The personal guardians of the hive's queen, these kalphites are far bigger than regular soldiers.

name: Kalphite Queen Form
dex_entry: Each kalphite hive needs a queen. And upon reaching a point in their life, they change form to become better at combat.

name: Kalphite Queen Mega Form
dex_entry: The true form of the queen of the kalphites. Only to be seen by players daring to enter the kalphite hive.

name: Kalphite Paragon Form
dex_entry: A small set of kalphites were deemed warped by the hive and was thus exiled. These were some of them.

name: Kalphite Corrupted Form
dex_entry: Giving in to the power and control of the devourer the kalphite has lost all reason and will of its own.

name: Kalphite Marauder Form
dex_entry: Outrider of its exiled clans they attack anything they can see that isnt kalphite shaped.

name: Kalphite King Form
dex_entry: A corrupted kalphite that has become warped. Capable of things a regular kalphite king would never be able to do.

name: Kalphite Dung Form
dex_entry: Blessed by Scabaras himself these small kalphites rolls balls of dung all day. Sometimes gems gets stuck in the dung.

name: Kalphite Reanimated Form
dex_entry: The head of a slain kalphite reborn anew. Only to be slain anew once more.

name: Abyssal Demon Reanimated Form
dex_entry: Once serving a hivemind of the abyss it has now broken free of the chain. But the new freedom confuses it.

name: Bat Gauntlet Corrupted Form
dex_entry: Corrupted beyond recognition the once shining crystals now spark a stunning red.

name: Bat Gauntlet Crystalline Form
dex_entry: A bat adornign beatifull crystals. It has trouble flying due to their weight.

name: Bloodveld Reanimated Form
dex_entry: It once sucked blood to survive, stripped of this power it finds little purpose in its new life.

name: Dark Beast Gauntlet Corrupted Form
dex_entry: Its hard to corrupt what is already a beast beyond control, but somehow the Gauntlet did this.

name: Dark Beast Gauntlet Crystalline Form
dex_entry: Its body adorned with crystal shining in so many colours its hard to recognice it as dark.

name: Dark Beast Pup Form
dex_entry: Small yet deadly these beings lurk where light cannot hit them.

name: Dark Beast Normal Form
dex_entry: Beasts lurking near the temple of light. Apparently they herald the return of the dark lord.

name: Dark Beast Sotetseg Form
dex_entry: A dark beast trained to perfection, its power is so dark no light shines.

name: Experiment 4 Form
dex_entry: Its head left intact but without a voice to talk. Its unknown how intelligent it remains but hopefully its mindless.

name: Experiment 5 Form
dex_entry: Despite being a spider this spider is strange because it has three joints instead of two like regular spiders.

name: Ganodermic Beast
dex_entry: This huge beast posesses thick layers of spores and rotten flesh protecting it from harm.

name: Grifolapine
dex_entry: The spikes on its body works as a defence to turn away predators, sadly it is a predator itself.

name: Grifolaroo
dex_entry: A ramokee gave life to these otherwise insignificant beings and they now work at his command.

name: Sporaxe
dex_entry: Once posessed by a spirit the axe finds a new use posessed by spores.

name: Headless Beast
dex_entry: Despite losing its head this unidentified beast keeps spreading terror, despite having no fangs.

name: Behemoth Normal Form
dex_entry: Despite not yet being of immense size, it will one day grow to be a beast feared by all.

name: Behemoth Adolscent Form
dex_entry: Trained from young age by Bilrach the Mahjarrat these beasts are to one day serve his god.

name: Siege Beast
dex_entry: Chosen by the god Zamorak these beasts laid waste to Saradomins armies in Lumbridge.

name: Bulwark Beast
dex_entry: With a body made of solid rock and minerals a pickaxe does more damage to it than swords.

name: Behemoth Gluttonous Form
dex_entry: Being locked in the cold floors of Daemonheim makes its metabolism spike, causing massive overeating.

name: Behemoth Runebound Form
dex_entry: To controll it Bilrach and his armies bound this behemoth down with runic energy to make it obey.

name: Stomp
dex_entry: Its body is so big it could not pass entirely into Gielinor, were the portal to close it would die.

name: Hope Devourer
dex_entry: It feeds on the hope and dreams of other. The warrior Marmaros got his hope eaten by this beast.

name: Karamthulu Overlord
dex_entry: The overlord of everything lurking the sea. All in its domain must pay homage to the overlord.

name: Light Creature
dex_entry: Beings of pure light attracted to any light of peculiar colours.

name: Minotaur Reanimated Form
dex_entry: A minotaur cursed to live in the darkness, now cursed to live reanimated.

name: Monkey Reanimated Form
dex_entry: Reanimated from its slumber or death, the monkey now sees little use but to die once more.

name: Rat Gauntlet Corrupted Form
dex_entry: A rat made entirely of corrupted crystals. They only find a home in the Gauntlet.

name: Rat Gauntlet Crystalline Form
dex_entry: As it walks around the gauntlet its body shimmers with light until an adventurer kills it.

name: Rat Fungal Form
dex_entry: Its now dead body plays host to a fungus. The fungus has reanimated the body as its own.

name: Sparky
dex_entry: After getting shot in its legs its nut stealing days were over. But the ranger who shot it helped it survive.

name: Spider Corpse Form
dex_entry: A spider taking host inside of a corpse. Its arms now spring forth from the corpse.

name: Spider Fever Form
dex_entry: Found near brew and rum distilleries these spiders bite pirates, making them sick and feverish.

name: Spider Lava Form
dex_entry: They only lurk around lava giving them their name, but its unknown why they are in the Dragonkin laboratories.

name: Spider Shadow Form
dex_entry: Invisible to the naked eye these shadow spiders lurk in the dark to assasinate and eat their prey.

name: Stalker
dex_entry: Their huge eyes are made to inform their father planet of what they see.

name: Soulseeker
dex_entry: Born of a sentient planet to convey sight these monsters stare at everything they find.

name: Stalker Sentinel Form
dex_entry: With one gigantic eye its said they can see things human eyes can not.

name: Night Gazer
dex_entry: It hates light so much it will viciously attack anything not in total darkness.

name: Plane Freezer
dex_entry: Its powers are so immense that anything around it freezes to solids within seconds.

name: World Gorger
dex_entry: Marked as remarkeable because as a stalker it posesses no extravagant traits. Just pure immense power.

name: Flesh Monger
dex_entry: It carries five younglings on its back. When it dies the five spawns eat their host and evolve.

name: Shadow Forger
dex_entry: It prefers to fasten itself in air above alcoves, killing anything near it with immense bursts of light.

name: Veil Ripper
dex_entry: Its powers are so immense that it can cut the veils of atoms to instantly create fire where it looks.

name: Unicorn Gauntlet Corrupted Form
dex_entry: Hailing from the gauntlet these corrupted unicorns stand out from their crystalline counterparts.

name: Unicorn Gauntlet Crystalline Form
dex_entry: Pure as the light that strikes them, these crystalline unicorns walks around the Gauntlet.

name: Wolf Cave Form
dex_entry: They lead their young trough cave systems hunting for mice and other prey.

name: Wolf Dragon Form
dex_entry: A merging of drgaon and wolf grown to its apex. The dragonking were apparently displeased with the result.

name: Shadow Hound
dex_entry: Hardly corporeal this beastly dog attacks any adventurer entering its domain.

name: Border Collie
dex_entry: A dog used to herd sheep. But for the most part they enjoy a nice snooze near the fireplace.

name: Bloodhound
